How this maps to real AMVs:

    Real AMVs are derived by tracking features such as clouds or water-vapor patterns through sequential satellite imagery, rather than by directly measuring wind.

    The JMA MTSAT system used three successive images and separate channels/bands for different AMV products.

    Operational systems also estimate height assignment and use quality indicators / thinning / bias control, which this toy simulator does only crudely.

To make this more realistic, the next upgrades would be:

    read real geostationary data from NetCDF/HDF5/GRIB,

    use IR or water-vapor brightness temperature fields instead of synthetic clouds,

    add a pressure/height assignment model,

    implement triplet consistency checks using all three frames,

    export vectors as lat/lon, u/v, pressure, QI.

